{
  "doc_id": "35957",
  "text": "The Institute of Medicine and Healthy People 2010 [CITATION_1] identify childhood obesity as a serious nationwide health problem requiring urgent attention in the United States. An estimated 10 million children are overweight, a number that has doubled in the past 20 years [CITATION_2] , with the prevalence of overweight in infancy increasing from 11% to 17% [3] . Obesity is more prevalent in lowerincome and minority children, placing them at increased risk for later health problems, such as hypertension, cardiovascular disease, and type II diabetes [CITATION_3] .",
